<HEADLINE> Pak to Hold National Education Convention Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will hold a national
education convention on February 21 for eliciting opinions of
experts and educationists on a new education policy.
</P>
<P>
This was decided on Friday at a cabinet meeting chaired by
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, the official Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided to constitute a cabinet committee to
formulate a comprehensive and practical education policy in
consonance with the national requirements and the demands of the
contemporary world, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The committee, which will be headed by Education Minister Syed
Ghous Ali Shah, is expected to submit its report before the
cabinet on January 21 for further discussion and deliberation on
the new policy.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the new education policy would be
finalized in the light of the recommendations, ideas and proposals
emerging from the national convention.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the meeting also emphasized the need to restore
dignity and honor of teachers, and to give them dignified and
well-deserved place in the society, the report noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
