<HEADLINE> OA Chairman of Board Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Emmanuel Fthenakis, chairman of
the board of Greece's national carrier Olympic Airways (OA),
submitted on Friday his resignation for not being supported by the
New Democracy (ND) members of parliament.
</P>
<P>
Fthenakis, who was first appointed to the board in 1993 under
the then ND government of Prime Minister Constantine Mitsotakis,
was approved recently for a second term by the relevant
parliamentary committee.
</P>
<P>
In his letter of resignation to Greek Transport and
Communications Minister Tassos Mantelis, Fthenakis said that he
decided to resign because the ND MPs on the relevant parliamentary
committee that approved his nomination had not voted for him, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The new chairman of the board would be selected within this
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
