<HEADLINE> Romania Reacts Strongly to Former King's Restoration Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Political parties and
organizations in Romania have reacted very strongly to a
restoration attempt by former King Mihai I.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Mihai's news office declared that he has chosen his
oldest daughter Margareta to "ascend the throne".
</P>
<P>
The Social Democratic Party of Romania, the largest opposition,
condemned Mihai's move as against the will of more than 90 percent
of the Romanians who support a republican political system, while
the Agrarian Democratic Party urged the highest authorities to
decide quickly on Mihai's legal status.
</P>
<P>
To clear the situation, the ruling National Peasant's Party
announced that it would take its position on the matter as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Mihai, 76, has been in exile overseas since he gave up his
throne in 1947, but indicates that he plans to return to live in
Romania recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
