<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Condemns Latest Massacre in Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
today strongly condemned the massacre of over 100 innocent people
in the outskirts of Bujumbura in Burundi on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the OAU said, Salim has learnt with
shock and deep regret of the tragic massacres of over 100
civilians including women, children and the elderly.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief strongly condemned these brutal acts as totally
unacceptable. "No cause can justify these wanton killings," Salim
said.
</P>
<P>
The latest tragedy in Burundi is a grim reminder on the need
to intensify efforts at finding a just and lasting solution to
the conflict in that country, the release noted.
</P>
<P>
The new year should provide the opportunity to reinvigorate
the peace process in that country so that dialogue and
negotiations can be pursued more vigorously and an end be put to
the senseless and costly violence, the release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
