<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Condemns Attack on Bujumbura Airport in Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- France today firmly condemned the
attack launched by Hutu rebels upon the Bujumbura airport in
Burundi on Thursday, in which more than 200 people, most of them
civilians, were killed.
</P>
<P>
"It appears more urgent than ever that a constructive dialogue
be installed between all the Burundian parties with a view for the
return of peace and national reconciliation of Burundi," said a
French Foreign Ministry spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that France supports the efforts by
President Pierre Buyoya of Burundi in favor of peace and
reconciliation, and appeals to Burundi's neighbors to create a
climate of peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Some 200,000 people, mostly civilians, have been killed in an
ethnic war in Burundi between the Hutu majority and
Tutsi-dominated military government, since the assassination of
President Melchior Ndadaye in October 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
