<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
today denied reports that it will hold joint military exercises
with Turkish Navy next week, UAE's Wam news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Wam quoted an official from the UAE's Defense Ministry as
saying that the reports by some foreign media on joint naval
exercises between the UAE Navy and a Turkish fleet, possibly to be
held next week in the Omani Sea, were "not true."
</P>
