Turkish President Suleyman Demirel's visit to the UAE earlier last
month.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and the UAE signed a military cooperation agreement in
1995. Demirel told reporters during his visit that the agreement
between the two countries had no difference with the military deal
Turkey clinched with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish-Israeli military agreement signed earlier last year
caused serious concerns among the Arab world. However, Turkey said
the military deal "is just a military training pact...and it is
not aimed at damaging the interests of any other state."
</P>
<P>
"Ankara has signed with 28 countries, including the UAE,
military cooperation deals and the agreement (with Israel) is
just one of them," Demirel had said. 
