<HEADLINE> Britain to Have Constructive Ties with Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 2 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said today that Britain would establish constructive relationship
with Argentina, but he also promised to protect the freedom of
Falkland (Malvinas) residents.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a New Year message to the British colony, Blair
said: "I want to develop our relations with Argentina, an
important country and a trading partner of Britain. I want us to
have an open and constructive relationship."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Blair expressed his conviction of protecting
security and freedom of the Falkland (Malvinas) islanders, saying
the Labor government had demonstrated its support for the 2,500
Falklanders' right of self-determination.
</P>
<P>
