committed to protecting your right to choose your way of life," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Argentine President Carlos Menem, due to visit London later
this year, reportedly said recently that he would discuss the
issue of shared Falklands (Malvinas) sovereignty with British
government leaders.
</P>
<P>
However, British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook has later ruled
out the possibility of shared sovereignty without the agreement of
local residents.
</P>
<P>
