<HEADLINE> French Gov't Offers Discount Transport Card to Jobless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The French government today said
that it would offer a discount transport card to the jobless
people to let them ride trains and buses at half normal fare
prices in the Paris region from early this year.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Transport Jean-Claude Gayssot made the announcement
after meeting with union and anti-unemployment movement
representatives.
</P>
<P>
The measure, which will benefit 270,000 people and will cost
the government 390 million francs (65 million U.S. dollars), is to
be subjected to approval by the unions of transport workers of the
Paris region later this month.
</P>
<P>
The government gesture came after a series of protests against
unemployment were staged in France during the Christmas and New
Year season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
