<HEADLINE> One Killed by Tempest Striking Western France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- One man was killed and two injured
by a violent tempest which struck the western part of France
Thursday night and today, said local media reports.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the wind destroyed many electricity power lines and
deprived 500,000 people of electricity. Some 30,000 homes in
Bretagne and 20,000 in the Loire-Atlantic region are not expecting
electricity supply restored by Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts predict new tempests in western France in the
coming days, while an alarm is maintained until Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Road and train transports were seriously disrupted in western
France by the tempest. Many trees, roofs of houses, placards and
vehicles were thrown up by the wind, whose speed attained 192
kilometers per hour. 
</P>
