<HEADLINE> Guangdong Saw Good Rural Economic Growth in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China produced 87.3 billion yuan from its rural economy in 1997,
up by 5.7 percent over that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The average rural resident earned 3,375 yuan in 1997, a real
growth of three percent over last year, according to the provincial
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The province harvested a record 19.6 million tons of grain, the
fourth successive year in agricultural gains.
</P>
<P>
The province, one of the richest in China, invested nearly 600
million yuan in poverty relief projects in 1997. The basic needs
for food and clothing of 600,000 people were met over the help
from local governments at various levels in the
province. Guangdong is one of the few provinces and autonomous
regions where nearly everyone has a living standard above the
poverty line.  
