<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-State Economy Becomes Active Element in Ningxia Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- With a boost from
foreign-funded and private enterprises in northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the non-state economy has become
the most active element of the area's economy.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that private and foreign-funded enterprises
paid 310 million yuan in taxes to the government in 1996,
accounting for a quarter of the whole region's local revenue.
</P>
<P>
Lu Chongguang, a regional official, said the non-state economy
has developed rapidly since 1992. The number of private businesses
approached 100,000 at the end of last October, with an annual
increase of 30 percent in employees, registered capital, total
output value and sales revenue. Last year, the numbers and output
value of share-holding and foreign-funded enterprises were three
times that of 1992.
</P>
<P>
As China's only Muslim concentration, the Hui nationality
people, accounting for one third of the region's population, have
a long business tradition. Regional government issued regulations
and gave preferential policies to encourage self-employed laborers.
</P>
<P>
The region's government invested 100 million yuan in setting up
and expanding more than 130 trade fairs, which assisted 80 percent
of self-employed businessmen in entering markets directly.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the region has more than 120 private
enterprises involved in agriculture with an investment of 100
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region has 378 private enterprises with registered capital
of one million yuan each, 51 with more than five million yuan
each, and 21 with fixed assets of more than 10 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Private technology became an investment magnet. The region's
technology department approved and listed 315 private technology
enterprises in the annual plan in such fields as computers,
chemicals, agriculture and medicine. These enterprises generated
an annual revenue of 200 million yuan and 16 million yuan in
profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
