<HEADLINE> Iran Earns 2 Billion Dollars in Non-Oil Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran earned about 2.066 billion
U.S. dollars from non-oil exports in the eight months of the
current Iranian fiscal year (from March to November 1997), local
newspaper Etelaat said today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a report from the Industries Ministry as
saying that 5.377 million tons of various non-oil goods were
exported during the period, showing a 16.3 percent increase in
weight and 2.3 percent increase in value from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
It said that export of industrial goods accounted for 39
percent of the country's total non-oil exports over the past eight
months, fetching some 814 million dollars, a 14.3 percent increase
from the same period of last Iranian year.
</P>
<P>
However, Iran's oil revenues registered 10 billion dollars in
the same period, far less than expected in the government budget,
Iranian Oil Minister Bijan Zanganeh had announced.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that with the current trend continuing till
the end of this Iranian year (March 1998), the country would only
earn some 15 billion dollars from oil exports, about 15.25 percent
below the budget level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
