<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gunman Shoots at Iraqi Diplomat in Amman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- A gunman shot at an Iraqi
diplomat here this morning, but failed to harm him, the Jordanian
Public Security Department announced.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Commercial Counselor at the Iraqi Embassy here Abdul
Rahim Taher survived the attack that happened at 08:15 local time
(06:15GMT) when he was driving from his home to his office in
western Amman, according to an official statement from the
department.
</P>
<P>
The gunman in a rental purple Korean-made car fired one shot
at Taher with a silencer-equipped pistol but missed him, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
After the attack, the gunman and his driver sped away in
their car and the Iraqi diplomat kept driving. When he arrived
at the embassy, Taher found his vehicle had been hit, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the attack for which no one has claimed
responsibility was being investigated.
</P>
<P>
Acting Minister of State for Information Affairs Nasir Lawzi
said today that the government was very concerned about the
assassination attack and the police were looking for the car
everywhere in the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Lawzi also confirmed that no one was injured in the attack but
small scratches were left on the front of the diplomat`s car.
</P>
<P>
Anonymous officials at the Iraqi Embassy in Jordan today
accused "a third party" of trying to damage the relations between
Jordan and Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
