<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Residents of Shanghai and
Guangzhou, two of China's largest cities, chose to start the new
year by showing care for others or enjoying themselves at scenic
resorts.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 volunteers in red caps took to the bustling
streets of Shanghai today to collect donations for those in
difficulty.
</P>
<P>
The activity, sponsored by the Shanghai Municipal Charity
Foundation, is aimed at helping poor families get a good start for
the new year, said Chen Tiedi, chairwoman of the foundation.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen donation centers were set up throughout the city, and
municipal official took the lead in donating money.
</P>
<P>
"The donation move will foster a social tendency of assisting
the poor and those in need," Chen said, adding that the donated
money will be used to support 10,000 poor families before the
Chinese Lunar Year which falls on Jan. 28.
</P>
<P>
At the donation centers along Shanghai's downtown streets,
pedestrians were ready to drop money into donation-collecting bags.
</P>
<P>
"Most of my schoolmates have come to donate some pocket money,"
junior high school student Chen Zhao said. "We feel very happy to
show love for the poor families."
</P>
<P>
Many Guangzhou residents chose to start the new year by taking
expeditions with family members and friends.
</P>
