<HEADLINE> Countrywide Topographic Data Base Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China's military map can be
renewed more quickly now because of a new geographic information
system.
</P>
<P>
Establishment of a countrywide topographic data base with a
scale of 1-to-250,000 was completed officially today after 10
years of effort by the Headquarters of the General Staff of
the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the new data base, the best of its kind in
China, has the largest map scale, the most complete geographic
information, the most diversified applications and the most
precise spatial information.
</P>
<P>
With a personal computer anyone can easily search, add, renew
or delete geographic data, the system can help make economic
decisions, monitor the environment, optimize transportation
networks and conduct resource surveys, experts say. 
</P>
