<HEADLINE> Crimes in Bangladesh Increase in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- About 85,000 criminal activities
were recorded in Bangladesh last year, an increase of nearly 10
percent over that in 1996, said law enforcing agencies and the
Home Ministry Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,393 killings took place throughout the country,
about 25 percent higher than that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The number of dacoities in 1997 rocketed to 10,691, about 11
times that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The incidents of rioting in the country increased by 5.3
percent to 7,291 in 1997 from 6,921 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Incidents of rubbery recorded in the country last year stood at
1,707, 18.8 percent higher that in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Criminal experts attributed the increasing criminal activities,
especially among the young people, to acute poverty, unemployment,
insecurity and instability in the socio-political arena in the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
