are on their way to the capital kampala or eastern city of Jinja,
an immigrant official in Busia confirmed.
</P>
<P>
The Indians who just left Kenya are now staying in Tororo,
Jinja amd Mbale districts and Kampala with their relatives or
book hotels, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
Some of the Indians told the paper they left Kenya for
security reason in fear of possible violence in the wake of
election. Four people have died at Nakuru during election this
week. Kenya began its general elections on December 29 last year.
</P>
<P>
The general election campaigning in Kenya claimed tens of
lifes in the passing months in chaos throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Indians who dominate Kenya's business life have been targets
of robbery in times of violence and there have been reports about
Indians leaving the country well ahead of the election for fear
of violence.  
