over the last few years. This is seen by observers as an encouragement
to the Nigerian government as it has been under sanctions imposed by
the European Union three years ago over alleged human rights abuse.
</P>
<P>
To further promote the bilateral relations, Nigeria has decided to
make the French language the second official language of the
English-speaking country.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian government also contracted with a French company,
allowing it to carry out the maintenance work of one of its four
failed refineries.  
