recent statements aired both in Tehran and Washington for a
dialogue between the two belligerent countries.
</P>
<P>
On December 14 last year, Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
voiced Iran's readiness to have a dialogue with the "great
American people." In return, U.S. President Bill Clinton said that
he expected "nothing better than a dialogue" with Iran.
