<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Marine Exports up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's fishing and aquiculture
industry grossed 755 million U.S. dollars in exports in 1997, 85
million U.S. dollars more than that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ministry of fisheries attributed the growth to
market-oriented economic policies, the active participation of
businesses from different economic sectors in production and
exports, and the expansion of outlets.
</P>
<P>
Marine exports now account for one tenth of the whole country's
export value, ranking third after rice and crude oil.
</P>
<P>
Japan imported 65 percent of Vietnam's marine exports in 1996
but only 40.5 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In a move to develop the industry, a denmark-funded three-year
(1996-99) project to help Vietnam fisheries improve the quality
of export sea products and expand outlets is being effectively
implemented.
</P>
<P>
The project also supports the establishment of a Vietnam sea
product processing and export association to promote cooperation
between businesses in the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
