<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Petroleum Resources to Last Another 30 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's petroleum
resources can only meet the national requirement for another 20 to
30 years, the government's Electricity and Gas Supply Department
said in its publication "Guide on Efficient Use of Electricity for
Domestic Appliances".
</P>
<P>
The gas reserve in the country can sustain controlled
production for the next 50 to 60 years, according to the
publication available at public libraries and obtainable from the
department.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, Malaysia's oil reserve stood at 3.9
billion barrels while production was at 630,000 barrels per day
and its gas reserve was at 79.8 trillion standard cubic feet while
production was at 4 billion standard cubic feet per day.
</P>
<P>
According to the publication, 60 percent of energy generated in
Malaysia uses natural gas as fuel, making it the most important
fuel in electricity production.  
</P>
