<HEADLINE> East China Province Implements New Housing Reform Measure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- All departments and institutions
directly under the Shandong Provincial Government are not allowed
to distribute apartments as a form of welfare effective on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new housing reform measure will spread to more areas and,
by 1999, all institutions of the province will stop distributing
welfare apartments, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with this reform measure, welfare housing of
workers will be realized in the form of cash instead. Each
worker's monthly salary will rise in accordance with a certain
proportion effective January 1.
</P>
<P>
The increased sum of money, which is a form of housing subsidy
for individuals from the government, will be used to purchase or
build new housing apartments, make housing repairs and pay rent.
</P>
<P>
Local financial organizations will also offer mortgage loans to
encourage more wage earners to buy apartments, said local
officials.
</P>
<P>
Housing reform has been in practice in this east China province
for almost a decade. The province has practiced reform measures
such as marketing government-subsidized apartments and
establishing a public accumulative housing fund for wage earners.
</P>
<P>
So far, Shandong has pooled 4 billion yuan (482 million US
dollars)through the housing fund. The province has also sold
government-subsidized apartments with a combined floor space of 80
million square meters, making up 55 percent of the marketable
government-subsidized apartments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
