<HEADLINE> Ancient Province Attracting More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province recorded 540,000
overseas tourist arrivals and more than 25 million domestic
tourist arrivals in 1997. The number of trips by overseas visitors
represented an eight percent rise over 1996, and that of domestic
tourists was up 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
This northwest Chinese province, which is world-famous for its
ancient terra cotta soldiers and numerous other ancient sites of
historical interest, earned 225 million U.S. dollars through
international tourism, up 13.6 percent over 1996, and 6.7 billion
yuan (807 million US dollars) through domestic tourism, a 10
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Among the tourists from overseas, Chinese compatriots from
Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao, and overseas Chinese registered the
biggest increases.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province, which is situated on the ancient silk
road, received more than 30 percent domestic tourists and
businessmen, epitomizing the province's increasing attraction as a
new economic hub. 
</P>
