<HEADLINE> Shelter-forest Project Proves Fruitful  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The shelter-forest project in
north, northeast and northwest China has produced fruitful outcome
after some 20 years of construction.
</P>
<P>
In the northwestern, northern and northeastern regions of the
country, there are 1.49 million square meters of desert, the Gobi
desert and desertified land, making up 98 percent of the country's
total.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government launched a three-phase shelter-forest
project in these regions in 1978 to help improve the local
environment as well as living conditions for local residents. The
project was planned to be completed in the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
According to an official in charge of the project, more than 20
million hectares of trees have been planted, with the forest
coverage rate rising to 9 percent from 5.05 percent in 1977, the
year preceding the reform and opening-up was launched in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Twenty percent of desertified land in the regions is subjected
to grave threat by wind and sand storms. approximately 40 percent
of soil-eroded land in the Loess Plateau has now been improved. In
agricultural areas, 65 percent of farmland has been under the
protection by criss-crossed forest belts, and more than 50
counties have built a regional shelter-forest network.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some one million hectares of forest in the project
area guarantees a fuel supply for more than 6 million households
of farmers and herdsmen.
</P>
<P>
The project has not only improved the local environment, but
helps to increase grain production. In the Gansu Corridor of
northwest China's Gansu Province alone, 52,000 hectares of sandy
area have been turned into high-yield farmland, with the combined
grain output of 2.22 billion kilograms, an increase from 1.72
billion kg in 1978.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980103.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shelter-forest Project Proves Fruitful  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Gansu Corridor, with less than 20 percent of the province's
arable land, produces 70 percent of Gansu's total commodity grain
output.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the shelter-forest project helps the development of
forestry and sideline industries in the project areas. Pengyang
County in northwestern Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region has helped
one-fifth of local farmers shake off poverty by planting apricot
trees.
</P>
<P>
Gansu Province scored a net income of more than 10 billion yuan
(1.2 billion U.S. dollars) from forestry in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Timber reserves in the project regions exceed 200 million cubic
meters with an annual timber output of 8 million cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the century, the forest coverage rate in the
afforested area in the north, northeast and northwest China
should exceed 10 percent, with 30 percent of the desertified land
improved, 50 percent of soil-eroded area under effective control,
and more than 80 percent of farmland brought under the protection
of criss-crossed shelter-forests. 
</P>
