<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Surin
Pitsuwan will meet Malaysian officials across the border on Monday
to seek assistance in Thailand's crackdown on terrorists,
according to the Nation newspaper on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Surin will seek Malaysia's cooperation in extraditing suspects
and will urge that caution be exercised in granting Malaysian
citizenship to Thai Muslims, the newspaper quoted Thai Interior
Minister Sanan Khachornprasart as saying.
