<DOCNO> XIE19980103.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Construct Center for 21st Century Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The trans-century goal for
Chongqing, China's youngest municipality, is to turn itself into
an economic center serving Southwest China and the upper reaches
of the Yangtze River by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Xu Zhongmin, Chongqing vice-mayor, said at a seminar on
investment and development in central and western part of China
that Chongqing, covering an area of 82,000 sq.km. and a population
of 30.2 million, boasts unique regional advantages and tremendous
potential for progress within the frame work of China's overall
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The seminar on Investment and Development in Central and
Western China was held in Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province
recently.
</P>
<P>
With the regional advantage of connecting to the country's east
and west, Chongqing itself is rich in resources like natural gas,
coal, electric power, hydropower and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The mammoth Three Gorges Project, the large hydro-electric
construction in the world has created a gargantuan demand for
investment and consumption, Xu noted. Meanwhile, infrastructure
with emphasis on transportation, telecommunication and energy has
begun to take shape.
</P>
<P>
As southwest China's communication hub and an inland port,
thanks to China's "golden waterway", the Yangtze River, the
municipality sends goods to foreign countries directly via the
Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, the State has granted Chongqing special supports in
the spheres of finance, credit, investment projects and policies,
he noted. Its upgrading into a municipality directly under the
central government last March has given it a special position as
the vanguard in the development of central and western regions.
</P>
<P>
Xu went on to say that Chongqing will enter 21st century with
greater openness than ever before.
</P>
<P>
It will continue to give priority to agriculture and the three
backbone industries -- machinery, chemicals and metallurgy with
its machinery dominated by cars and motor cycles.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, special emphasis will also be placed on
such industries as electronic information, construction materials
and food processing.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the favorable policies foreign businessmen find in
coastal regions are available in Chongqing, Xu noted, adding that
the policies will be carefully implemented to provide good
services for investors in a freer environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
