<HEADLINE> Brazil Bans Import of Birds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government on
Friday banned any import of domestic or wild ornamental birds
without the authorization of the Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture and Livestock Defense Secretary Enio Marques of
the Agriculture Ministry announced the ban and said that was a
measure designed to prevent the spread of illnesses carried by the
birds in some countries last year.
</P>
