<HEADLINE> Alitalia to Court Singapore Airlines After KLM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Alitalia, the public-owned Italian
airline, is "looking with great interest" at Singapore Airlines as
a potential partner in Asia, Italian Transport Minister Claudio
Burlando said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
After Alitalia announced a strategic partnership on December 17
with the Dutch airline, KLM, its officials have said that the
conclusion of a deal with a European partner would be followed by
the search for a partner in Asia.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Roman daily, II Messaggero, Burlando
said the Asian partnership would be signed by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
He also said that, by the end of the year, the public stake in
the airline Alitalia should be reduced to 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
It is currently under the umbrella of Iri, the public holding
company.
</P>
<P>
The December 17 deal combines Alitalia's strengths in Europe
and Latin America, including on the Milan-Rome route, one of
Europe's busiest, with KLM's wider range of international
destinations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
