<HEADLINE> Frenchman Saby Maintains Lead in Paris-Dakar Auto Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Bruno Saby maintained
his lead in the car category of the Paris-Dakar auto rally after
the second day's competition on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Saby registered a time of 38 minutes 46 seconds on overall
standings after the 950-kilometer (590-mile) stage from Narbonne,
France to Grenada, Spain.
</P>
<P>
He was followed by fellow countryman Jean-Pierre Fontenay one
minute and 38 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Kenjiro Shinozuka was third 42 seconds further behind.
</P>
