overall standings at 38:22, 1:14 ahead of Italian Giovanni Sala in
second place.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Joan Roma placed third 1:33 slower than Fasola.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's course ends at the port of Almeria, Spain, from
where the racers will be ferry to the African continent.
</P>
<P>
The 10,245-kilometer rally will conclude on the traditional
stretch of beach in Senegal in about 16 days. 
