<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are news about
culture, arts and entertainment in recent days:
</P>
<P>
Painting, Sculpture Exhibition to Be Opened in Uruguay
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- An exhibition of Uruguayan paintings and
sculptures donated by painter Nicolas Garcia Uriburu will be
inaugurated Friday night in Maldonado, a city some 130 kilometers
east of the capital Montevideo.
</P>
<P>
The paintings and sculptures, collected by Uriburu during the
past 25 years, are works of Uruguay's best artists in
1880-1945. They are the original works of monuments that are in
public parks and on the facade of the Montevideo Cathedral.
</P>
<P>
TV Serial "El Barrio" Win Prize in Costa Rica
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- A Costa Rican television serial named "El Barrio"
(The Neighborhood) swept almost all the prizes given by local
media to the best television production of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Directed by veteran director Oscar Castillo, "El Barrio" put on
the screen typical characteristics of common people living in the
city.
</P>
<P>
Castillo collected the highest number of votes for the best
television director, and the serial was awarded other major
prizes, including the best production, the best actor (Andres
Montero and Gustavo Rojas), the best actress (Anabelle Ulloa) and
the best revelation of the year (Antonio Baker).
</P>
<P>
Pablo Neruda's Home Surroundings Declared Typical Zone
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The Chilean Education Ministry declared "typical
zone" the coastal area of Isla Negra, where the house of Chile's
late writer Pablo Neruda is located.
</P>
<P>
Neruda's home is a historical monument in Chile. It is in the
house that the poet wrote the most important part of his works.
</P>
<P>
The declaration of "typical zone" here is to protect
environment, architecture and the urban beauty of the landscape.
</P>
</TEXT>
