<HEADLINE> Doctors Remove Football-Sized Tumor From Man's Face </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Wang Xiaoyuan, a 59-year-old
patient with mental problems, successfully had a tumor removed
from the right side of his face that was the size of a football.
</P>
<P>
"This was the biggest tumor I have ever seen," said Dr. Zhang
Mengyin, the surgeon in charge of the operation at the Shanghai
Huashan Hospital. Two surgeons and a psychiatrist assisted Zhang
with the operation.
</P>
<P>
The tumor, which weighed three kilograms, had plagued the
mental patient Wang for more than two decades. Because of the
patient's resistance to treatment, the tumor grew from egg-size to
as big as his head. The patient could not hold his head upright
and was confined to bed.
</P>
<P>
Relatives of the patient had asked for help from many hospitals
but were turned down repeatedly for the dangerous and complex
operation owing to the size of the tumor.
</P>
<P>
After the operation, the patient was seen holding his head
upright again and having some smiles. He is now recovering well.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
