<HEADLINE> Chongqing Accelerates Process of Building Legal Framework </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, a major industrial
base, has stepped up the building of its legal framework since it
was upgraded to China's fourth municipality in March 1997, in a
bid to promote a healthy development of its economy.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government's first working conference on legality
which ended recently revealed that the municipality aims to set up
an overall legal framework which centers on economic development.
</P>
<P>
An official with the municipal government said that Chongqing
is presently concentrating on legislation to reform state-owned
enterprises and the removal and settlement of residents originally
residing in the Three Gorges Dam areas.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government attaches great importance to the
building of a highly efficient law-enforcement troop, which is
essential to the municipality's image as a major industrial city
in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to an newly promulgated regulation, law-enforcement
personnel who did not receive professional training and undergo
appraisals cannot begin their work as officers.
</P>
<P>
The city also plans to improve supervision of law-enforcement
as part of an effort to make the municipality's investment
environment more attractive, the official said. 
</P>
