<HEADLINE> East China Province Focuses on Land-Use Legislation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Fujian Province, east China, has
stepped up legislation on land administration and strengthed
enforcement of land laws since early last year.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial bureau of land administration
said that, in the first half of 1997, the province drafted
regulations on the management of cultivated land and land with
disputed ownership.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the provincial legislative body surveyed land
not used for agricultural purposes, and several regulations on
their management were soon drafted and have now become effective.
</P>
<P>
The official said that to ensure the smooth implementation of
these new regulations the provincial bureau of land administration
set up a special supervision team, which then placed several major
land cases on file for investigation.
</P>
<P>
The provincial land administration bureau is also outlining an
interim regulation on land-related cases which should be
transferred to judicial departments for further investigation and
prosecution, the official added. 
</P>
