<HEADLINE> China's Retail Sales on Quick Increase last October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China's retail sales amounted
to 234.8 billion yuan last October, up 11.6 percent over the
correspondent period in 1996, said the latest statistics from
State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The top three consumers were Guangdong, Jiangsu and Shandong
provinces, of which the retail sales amounted to 25.9 billion
yuan, 17.6 billion yuan and 15.9 billion yuan, respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
