<HEADLINE> China's Retail Prices Slightly Down Last October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The retail sales price index of
China stood at 99.6 last October, taking that of the same period
of 1996 as 100, according to the latest statistics from State
Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The biggest price increases emerged in the sales of fresh
vegetable, of which the index hit 109.2.
</P>
<P>
The biggest prices decrease was was in the sales of books,
newspapers and magazines, of which the index was 107.9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
